org.icepdf.core.pobjects.acroform

Class VariableTextFieldDictionary

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.icepdf.core.pobjects.Dictionary
      • org.icepdf.core.pobjects.acroform.FieldDictionary
        • org.icepdf.core.pobjects.acroform.VariableTextFieldDictionary
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ButtonFieldDictionary, ChoiceFieldDictionary, TextFieldDictionary

    public class VariableTextFieldDictionary
extends FieldDictionary
    When the contents and properties of a field are known in advance, its visual appearance can be specified by an appearance stream defined in the PDF file (see 12.5.5, "Appearance Streams," and 12.5.6.19, "Widget Annotations"). In some cases, however, the field may contain text whose value is not known until viewing time.
    Since:
    5.1

      • generateDefaultAppearance

        public String generateDefaultAppearance(String content,
                                        Resources resources)
        If the DA key is present the appearance stream is generated as is, however if not then the content is passed and we try to pull the color, size, font, and font name.
        Parameters:
        content - content to parse for general appearance values.
        resources - parent resource dictionary.
        Returns:
        base postscript encoded default appearance values.
